<rate>1<//rate>< text>
I took my African Grey for boarding. I have used them before in the past and never had an issue. She was staying at the Torrance location, because they had construction going on at the Carson location.

When I pulled up they were bringing  her in. Once they brought her to me I checked her bowls and they were filthy dirty! I was so upset. I left instructions to clean her bowels two or three times a day. There was bird fences on her food.

The water bowl was full of residue.  There is no way they had cleaned her bowls as I instructed. One of her foot toys was on the cage floor covered in feces.

I spoke to the manager named Natly.  She had a very nonchalant attitude  and was not apologetic. She glanced at the bowls and said I will speak to the staff. I asked who was her supervisor and she said the doctors.  I asked to speak with one of them. She said they would be in at 3:00pm. There was a man standing in the back with sunglasses on watching, but didn't say anything.

When I got home I looked them up online to see who where the doctor's.  The docotor was there the entire time!  He didn't say a word. They have several locations Carson, Torrance and Montery Park.  Dr. Nesha was at the Montery Park location that day. I spoke with her and expressed how upset I was. She claims that her staff washed her bowls twice a day and that Nataly was a very good manager.  I let her know I didnt appreciate that her partner was there and didn't step up when I asked to speak with Nataly's supervisor. She made an excuses for why he didn't didn't step in.

I told her there is no way the bowls were cleaned as filthy as they were. She gave a dry apology and asked what would I like her to do. I asked for a blood test to make sure she didn't have any type of Infection and not be charged. She said oh I can't do that! I was so angry I just hung up.< /text>

<GmapID>0x80dd3505eb95a667:0xfc679536ff5b68cc</GmapID><response>None</response><Rating>3</Rating>< review>
Good for small stuff, but don't board your pets there. The good thing is that they are reasonably convenient and pretty accommodating with the schedule. I get my dogs' nails trimmed and  get their vaccinations done there. The rest: You have to pay their office visit fee every time you go there, even if your pet is a regular, and even if it is a repeat procedure (my dog goes for allergy shots.) As another person wrote, their prices are pretty high for more involved procedures. But boarding is a no-no. Most vet clinics offer boarding but are not good at it. I think it's because they look at pets as patients and not as companions like real boarding facilities do. Your pet is kept in a caged 3x6-foot (approx. area) kennel with a cold concrete floor. They offer no bedding, toys, music or company. It's just a big storage room for pets. No one spends time with your pet other than to walk them occasionally. Frankly, it's like jail. Spend the extra money and take your pet to a dedicated boarding facility.<//review>

<rating>1< /rating><time>1537926335276</time>< text>
Extremely unhappy with the service. Last year, I brought my dog here for a severe ear infection that caused her so much pain that made her whimper. They informed us that they wouldnt be able to see her, and that their next availability would be 2 weeks. Explained the severity, but they didn't even care. They didn't even offer for me to wait to see if there were any availability or to place my dog on a waitlist. They strictly dismissed us. This was when I took my dog to another vet where they offered me the option to wait due to how busy they were, but still have my dog be seen. They offered better service which made the wait time worth it; this is how a vet should respond to an urgent matter.
Avalon Animal Hospital is just a joke and poor excuse of a facility. If you truly care for the well-being of your pet, than avoid this place at all cost.<//text>

You are contemplating plastic surgery, correct?  All the "what if's?" and "how much?" thoughts are flitting through your mind.  If my review can assist you in deciding upon a procedure with a reputable, highly skilled, nay, "artist", then consider Dr. Miguel Delgado's expertise and talent to make you look like the woman you want to be.  Whatever your reasons, for me it was restoring my neck and lower face to what it was when younger, this could be the opportunity you are seeking.  After seeing various local surgeons and assessing their "cookie cutter" suggestions and portfolios, I delayed my decision.  Upon visiting his clinic for an unrelated procedure, I thought why not review his lookbook and was immediately impressed.  So subtle and yet definitely, sags and bags vanished in the "after" pictures without stretching or obvious signs of "having work done."  The results made the individuals look "rested and relaxed."  What was the price of such expertise was my next thought.

Comparing previous surgery done several years ago, as well as current fees, I realized the cost was extremely competitive.  (Third-party financial packages are also offered.)  Another factor was the outstanding surgery team (I have certain health issues which were addressed).

Finally, post-operative care is another concern.  This is not a doctor who removes tubes and stitches and waves good-bye. Rather, several follow-up visits ensured proper healing was taking place.

The end result is, I am absolutely pleased.  My face around my mouth is contoured to a youthful self, my neck and area beneath my chin no longer fall into folds or sagging wrinkles.  Dr. Delgado understood I wanted a smooth, natural lower face and sculpted accordingly.

I hope my personal experience assists you in your search for the "right" plastic surgeon.  A free consult visit is the only way to find out.</review>

< review>
Here's summary of 2017 Delgado Family Pinot tasting by 4 family members:

Starbright garnet color with consistent color from core to rim. The nose has notes of bright red fruits and tart red fruits like red cap berries. At the same time, there is an ever-present aroma of white or ash smoke. The ash and lightly toasted oak remains consistent on the palate. The acid of the wine is lively which helps balance the higher alcohol percentage. Overall, from color to finish, a pretty true-to varietal and appellation pinot noir.

Good value dinner wine: Strongly recommended< /review>

BOTOX ONLY REVIEW : I waited two weeks to give the readers a through review. I googled plastic surgery in Novato and this place came up. I booked with Nurse Ariel. < Review>
I spent most of my teens and early twenties (I'm 25 now) hiding. Not like under a bed or in a trashcan in a park, but just... hiding, trying to make myself invisible. All those baggy shirts, all the time I spent slouching, all those hugs I rejected because I felt incredibly self-conscious... it was to hide my gynecomastia. I tried so hard to get rid of it through exercise. I became a trail runner, regularly running 5-7 miles, and I performed hundreds of push ups every week. Even though my health is probably really good because of it, my gyno only became more prominent. For every extra mile, for every bench press or pushup, I became a little bit more frustrated. At the end of the day, gynecomastia precluded a normal life for me. So I did what I didn't think I would ever do - gynecomastia surgery. I vetted a couple of doctors, but Dr. Delgado gave me comfort in knowing that I was in experienced hands. It has been about 4 weeks since my surgery, and I can say without a doubt a new chapter has been started. There aren't words to express the myriad of positive emotions that I am feeling, but maybe this little experience might illustrate it, especially for those of you who can relate. I have a Hollister shirt that was gifted to me a couple of years ago. I have never worn it in public, because well, Hollister shirts stick to every nook, cranny, and moob. Once my swelling subsided and I could take off the vest for a minute, I decided to try it out. When I saw myself in the mirror, I began to smile and laugh uncontrollably!!! I think I got a little teary eyed too! I lived trying to hide for most of my life, but when I saw myself in that mirror, I realized that I wouldn't have to anymore. Dr. Delgado, I am sure you get this quite often, but thank you so very much, you really have changed my life.<//Review>

< Text>
I had a wonderful experience with Dr. Delgado's aesthetic nurse Ariel Kirk. I had always preferred surgery over injectables but I was impressed with the results. There are definitely advantages since there is minimal planning and down time and many of the injectables are lasting longer. I had filler placed in my cheeks, around my mouth and eyes. The results were fabulous. My cheeks were fuller, lifting the focus on my face with a more youthful appearance and reviving areas of lost fat. With addition of filler around my mouth, many wrinkles diminished or disappeared and added fullness to my ageing face. The procedures are quick and done in an office appointment. There was minimal discomfort on injection, Ariel uses local and is gentle. The sting on injection is much less than my dental procedures and results immediate. My biggest problem was swelling, definitely ice is the best for that. Some people have more brusing than others but that fades quickly and Arnica helps. Simple, easy, and fast results. I was excited having it done and I'm euphoric with the results. Thank you, Ariel.</Text>

I had a wonderful experience with Dr. Miguel Delgado and his staff. On March 21, 2013 I underwent a full tummy, waist enhancement, and liposuction of the flanks.   I have to say my experience far exceeded my expectations!  On our first visit we discussed my challenging medical history ‚Äì diabetes, high blood pressure and asthma, and determined the next steps to ensure a safe surgery.  During my pre-op appointment we went through how to prepare for surgery, what to expect during the surgery, and possible complications.  I was very happy that Dr. Delgado had me prepare by starting a ‚ÄúClinical Support Program‚Äù that includes vitamin supplements & homeopathic remedies, and he encouraged colon hydrotherapy.   My surgery was a success!!  I felt supported during the entire process.  Dr. Delgado called once a day for a few days to see how I was doing, and I went in once a week for a few weeks for check ups. <time>1384892148030<//time><Name>R. Green</Name><Review>Let me just start by saying, "I adore Dr. Miguel Delgado."

Okay, so what's my story? Since I was a young lady, I always knew I wanted to have a full figure. I was never going to have it naturally--I wasn't built that way. And after having my son and two surrogacy pregnancies, my breasts had decided to become even thinner, saggier, and smaller (as if that was even possible). When it came time to do the research, Dr. Delgado was top on the list. But unfortunately I was with someone who recommended I use a different doctor. I chose to follow his direction. That was five years ago.

I was never fully satisfied with my first augmentation. There was very little consultation, no recommendation of what type of implants to use, and very little preparation or direction. While the staff was friendly and the doctor was knowledgable, I was left feeling a little in the dark.

Fast forward to today: it was time for a revision. It was time to get the size I really wanted (smaller) and repair my keloid scar on the left nipple. I spoke with the Dr. Delgado's team who recommended I make an appointment for a consultation, which I did. And thank goodness! Dr. Delgado is wonderful. He is kind, sincere, and extremely talented.

What I had was a left breast that sat high due to keloid scarring on the nipple and poor pocket development. The right breast was relatively okay, in my eyes. I wanted smaller breasts, which he agreed would look good on my frame, and he suggested I get high profile as opposed to the medium profile I had originally used. He told me how he would be able to repair the left pocket and help create a more natural look using a matrix. (The scar tissue had left very little skin to work with once it was removed during the revision, so the matrix would make it possible to fix the problem). I felt excited and ready to take this step.

The second consultation before my surgery, Dr. Delgado did a thorough examination of my breasts, frame, and position. He gave me suggestions of the size of implant and style--both of which I followed. He also explained in detail the use of the matrix to correct the scarring and help create a natural look.

What is it like today? Today, I can wear whatever I want with as low a cleavage on a shirt as I want--and feel absolutely comfortable. I no longer look like I'm popping a shelf with fake boobies! They are so soft and have an amazingly natural sag (which I prefer) and I am thrilled with the end result! The recovery was smooth and amazingly easy. (That could be because it was a revision and less of a shock to my body this second time around--but I honestly believe Dr. Delgado has a technique that makes it so easy! I bounced back like I was 25 instead of 40!)

I'm sure this was far more detailed than you cared to read. But I wanted to be sure to show how Dr. Delgado worked miracles with me! His staff is wonderful and Colleen was absolutely fantastic--helping me count when I was too excited to be able to!

I am a new woman because of Dr. Delgado! And for that, I am eternally grateful!< /Review>< pictures>

< review>
MOMMY MAKEOVER

Shortly before my 40th birthday, I decided that my post-baby body needed quite a few repairs. I was determined to find the best plastic surgeon in the Bay Area, one that was extremely skilled and would not leave me with that scary, over-pulled ‚Äúdeer in the headlights‚Äù appearance.

Dr. Delgado, a Board Certified Plastic Surgeon in Marin, came highly recommended by friends and respected members of my community. He specializes in natural facial and breast surgery, liposuction and tummy tucks ‚Äìso I made an appointment for a consultation.

He was extremely professional during my appointment and we discussed many different options for me.  He took the time to explain all of the procedures, the recovery process ‚Äìand realistic expectations of the results.  He provided an unbiased opinion and did not push me into doing anything that I did not want or need.  His consultation was very informative and I felt very comfortable before ‚Äìand after surgery.

The procedures, which were performed in a private operating room located inside a hospital, were lengthy since I signed up for several procedures at once --but the outcome far exceeded my expectations. I was also comforted knowing that there is an emergency room a short distance away should any issues arise.

My recovery went well, and after the swelling went down and all of the stitches were removed, I was extremely pleased with the results. My face and body had a natural and even appearance that only a skilled doctor can provide ‚Äìwith scars that are barely visible. I love the way I look and feel!  Even 8 years later, I am still asked what my secret is to such a youthful appearance and I simply reply:

Part good genetics‚Ä¶ Part good products‚Ä¶ Part GREAT doctor!

Today, I maintain his amazing work by taking better care of myself (mind, body and spirit) and with the help of an occasional appointment in their facility ‚Äìincluding facials from their amazing esthetician Alise. She is very knowledgeable and I love the unique products that she recommends for my skin care needs.

They deserve a five star rating! Note, I have never written a review for a professional service, but I feel strongly that women, especially mothers, should know who should be on their team if they are contemplating this type of elective surgery or simple maintenance of what you already have.

Thank you to Dr. Delgado and his staff for an amazing experience!</review>

<Rate>5</Rate><Review>Everything about our expierence was wonderful. The service and staff were BEYOND nice. After arriving we drove a bit around town because the pilot and his staff were checking weather and wind conditions. We did not mind that one bit. The balloon ride itself was super smooth and relaxing, not what I was expecting. The landing was quite bumpy but I personally thought it was super fun. Brace for impact. I don't think anyone is hungry this early in the morning so the simple muffins and Danish are perfect. The champagne they serve after the ride during the intimate celebration is made by Europa winery and it is delicious. The mimosas offered are simple and delicious. I would recommend this company to family and friends and would use them again in the future. I think it is important to comment on the fact that we were not charged until after the ride and had a choice credit card or cash. Even though I made the reservation on my card I was able to pay cash. I think this is really great. The reason they do not charge until after the fact is because due to weather and wind conditions The ride can be canceled and so they avoid a lot of fuss having to refund people. Thanks guys for the wonderful expierence.<//Review>< pictures>

This was the most memorable thing we did on our 21 day tour of California and the western states. Temecula is GORGEOUS and to see the vineyards and orchards with the mountains all around. We thought it might be cold or windy and that couldn't have been further from the truth as the heat from the flame kept us very warm and there is no wind because you move at whatever speed the wind blows. Truly an awesome experience. Jeff was our pilot and he's flown balloons all over the world since he was little and he is extremely skilled and was able to land our basket full of people smoothly on the trailer when the flight was over. We were highly impressed. The breakfast (muffins/snacks, juice, champagne) gathering after the flight is also a really nice touch. I recommend this to everyone.</Review>

105092658195117649597< /user_id>
<name>Jen H<//name><date>1423252761465<//date>< rating>
4</rating>
<Text>-My first experience on a Hot Air Balloon-AM-

For those that are afraid of heights, I can relate. Overall, I was only scared for the first five minutes since its normal to psyche yourself out. When you're getting into the basket and the hot air balloon starts ascending, you will start to think, 'Holy crap, am I really doing this?!!' No Sweat....just take a few breaths and before you know it, you're in the sky enjoying a beautiful morning view. The balloon was steady enough to evaporate my fear.

In the basket, it's segregated into sections. If you have a big balloon, there will be four sections where four people can fit into each section. Our guide had the center section to himself in order to fly the balloon, total of five sections.

Recommended Attire:
Long pants and a light sweater (the heat from the hot air balloon will keep you warm; it's like having a heat lamp right above you).

Do bring a jacket and leave it in the van because you'll need it for the champagne picnic afterwards. Outdoor, back at Vineyard.

Bring sunglasses, unless you want to squint in all your photos!

Shoes: Closed toe that you don't mind getting dirty; the takeoff area is usually in a field with plenty of dirt.

They have various balloon and basket sizes. If you want privacy, it is available. In our group this morning, there was a couple with their own private balloon. After we all landed, we learned that there was a proposal on that private balloon, so romantic! Luckily, the girl said yes and we all celebrated with them at our champagne picnic afterwards. I didn't get a price for the private balloon, but for general admission is $145.

The picnic included some fruits (grape, oranges, and bananas) and wrapped pastries that seemed too sweet to me. Picnic also included champagne or mimosas. We were also handed some discounted wine tasting tickets for the Great Escape and Robert Rezoni, bonus!

Overall, I had a great time. My favorite part of this experience was overseeing the other hot air balloons with the fog rolling back, simply fantastic!< /Text>< Pics>
None</Pics>

<pictures>[{'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipMEALg-MUXu2TBcpvc_YSRiIpOfJhFgdiu79-T5=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipM36wAN1E8L3ZV-7DmHKg3RoW24LiXguPFs9P5r=w150-h150-k-no-p']}]</pictures><Response>None< /Response>< Gmap_id>

< userid>
105490479552294944372</userid>
< Name>
i leana<//Name>
< time>
1616006287991< /time>
<Rate>4</Rate><text>Apparently when we went, it was their first day back open for a while. Limited availability makes for a safer feeling trip. They now have an app for the audio tour for your phone as well as their supply of tour devices with earphones- I suggest you get those.

It was a long wait to start the timed tour due to social distancing, then when our app didn‚Äôt work, we tried to go back to the start to pick up devices- but being as it was the last tour of the day, they had already packed up. Luckily, we were able to grab a device from the drop-off @ the end of the tour, but we were out of time to do the whole thing & just walked through without the audio tour which was a bummer. Rangers will make sure no one is left behind before the last ferry leaves.

The ferry was nice, with lots of space, although not much enforcement of social distancing due to many people. More labeling on the ground and signage might help.

Still, definitely always fun to have a lil history trip in SF. In my opinion, the Native American feature should be a part of the Alcatraz tour and not optional- it‚Äôs down a different path to the right when you get there, past the fire engine. Also, maybe there should be some education of solitary confinement‚Äôs effects on mental health.

< name>
Aryan Batra<//name>
</record></dataset><record>
<text>David here,

Over the last decade I have been looking at the skeletal remains of my once proud skateboard, constantly telling myself to fix it up and get back to the sport I once loved so well. So today I did it, went into Street Science for a whole new setup, right off the bat MacKenzie welcomed me in and started guiding my way through the new brands.

I was amazed to find out all of my tried and true brands were dust in the wind, sold out to walmart and suffered huge reduction in quality, but MacKenzie was a big help in finding me the right deck for me (I felt bad because she took down about 15 and had to put them back up). In the end I got a really nice finished product that I look forward to testing on the streets. Still the same prices I grew to expect years ago which was a big plus. Awesome time today and I will be coming back for sure.

P.S. they give half pipe/vert lessons starting at $40 which is great for kids.< /text><gmapID>0x808fe79f994ddb69:0x61278d86c3531e99< /gmapID>< Name>
Noneya Bidniss< /Name>

<Review>These people gave me the BEST pedicure and shellac mani. I went here a few days before my wedding and got a pretty typical bridal set of nails (soft pink).

Let me just tell you- the shellac nails I got here lasted longer than the 50+ shellac manicures I've gotten over my lifetime. Seriously good stuff. My nails didn't chip AT ALL. EVER. Over time, the only way you could tell that my manicure wasn't new was because my nails grew out..so obviously just a natural occurrence.

The people at this salon were SOOO amazing and sweet. I brought a group of six women and they were able to accommodate all of us. We were in and out in 90 minutes and we all left very pleased with our services!!!

< text>
We've been coming here as a family (yep! Dad too!) for years. The staff is professional, welcoming, and their colors are organized by shade, which makes it so much easier; the color selection is great!

I have had both pedicures and manicures, and for each you see them open new utensils before starting. The default scent of the sugar scrub for the pedicure is lemongrass, which smells divine. The manicure came with an extensive arm and neck massage (which I appreciate but I was not aware was coming, so heads up if you're sensitive to touch outside a traditional massage).

Ask for a stamp card if they don't give you one, because you'll want to come back.< /text>

< user_id>
116265924203447239777< /user_id>
<user_name>909 RPh< /user_name><Time>1579152461111</Time><Rating>3</Rating>< Review>
Red Robin is... OK. They do a competent job with the burgers. I ordered the peppered bacon burger. On paper, along with extra sharp cheddar cheese described, it promised more than it delivered. You have a choice of cooking your hamburger medium or well. Mine was ordered medium and showed up much closer to well done. The bottomless fries are an appealing idea, but you are paying 15 bucks for the burger which includes them. The beer list is nothing to get excited about. My son did have a strawberry cream soda which was not nearly as sweet as I expected, and he seemed to enjoy it quite a bit. The staff was friendly and attentive. If I could give it three and a half stars I would have on the basis of the staff.< /Review>

<Name>KARSTEN POLK< /Name><Time>1564025248969<//Time><rate>5</rate>< Review>
Great burgers, bottomless fries, what more can you ask for. The service was good, and it was nice and cool inside; break from hot summer day. Seating was a little cramped, but it made for good comfort and coziness with the family. Our waitress tended frequently and seemed to address our needs before we had to ask for them. I call that great service. We got there at 430 and beat the dinner crowd, there was good parking, plenty of tables, and no wait time. Leaving about 530-6 we saw more and more people coming in. So if you like early supper, you'll avoid crowds. And again, I was really impressed with service.</Review>

<user_id>118067890871361839384<//user_id><gmap_id>0x80dcaa596f3c7043:0x62587003300b2e44<//gmap_id>< Review>
We have enjoyed, for many many years, the best cod fish and chips available anywhere at Red Robin. That was the main motive for visiting your restaurant. Sadly, the last two visits, especially the most previous one, caused great disappointment. The pieces or content of the fish has decreased noticeably as well as the quality. Our order of three plates of fish was heavy and thick with batter, giving a doughy taste. This is not a fluke. The decision makers at Red Robin are succumbing to the profit trap instead of maintaining your quality integrity that made YOU who you are. This is a sad day for Red Robin.</Review>

< Text>
Came to red robin on a slow Monday at 3:30pm. I was seated right away in the bar area. The server was nice and polite but that's all that was good about the trip. My girlfriend and I both ordered water. The cups were dirty and still had sticky, sugary residue on the inside of the cup that would fall into our water if we wiped it. We had ordered a royal robin burger cut in half to share and bottomless garlic fries. The cook brought our burger out but it was not cut in half and he just gave us an extra plate. That wasn't a big deal to us so we just cut the burger in half ourselves. When I tried to place the half of the burger on the other plate, it had cheese on the plate and was dirty. Then the cook brought us regular fries instead of the garlic ones we ordered. I told him and he went ahead and brought us our fries. The whole time our server was missing for ten minutes. We had to push the "call server" button on the ziosk to get her attention. I told her about the water and how dirty they were and she was polite and brought us new ones which were still dirty! Then we asked for more fries and she brought us regular fries again. We just accepted it and said we were never coming here again.<//Text>

If I could give this place negative stars I would! Me, my fiance, his mom, and a family friend all went there to eat and all 4 of us got so sick we all ended up throwing up in the parking lot. The fries we received with our meals and the second baskets that were brought out were cold and extremely old and stale. They were insanely greasy and all but burnt. We we're told the kitchen was closed but they would  make us fresh fries. These last ones came out hot and golden like they should have been so obviously what we got was far from fresh. The water was disgusting, it was cloudy, it smelled weirdand left a bad taste in the mouth. Of the 4 meals we got, 1 was missing things requested, 1 was totally overdone and all of them were definitely sitting out for a while because they weren't hot like they should have been. On top of all this, when we complained about the fries the server didn't even seem to notice and when the manager came over he acted like we ordered them extra crispy and that it was our fault. He took a couple dollars off  the bill and filed a report. When we all got sick before even making it to the car, and mind you we were parked front row next to a handicap spot, my fiance went back in to complain again. None of the staff asked if we were ok or anything, they just told us that the stores insurance will contact us and there's nothing they can do. They didn't care at all, they literally watched all of us getting violently sick and didn't care at all. I will never go back to this restaurant at all, they allow bad food to be served and don't do anything about it getting customers sick. Disgusting, absolutely disgusting. Never go here, spend your money elsewhere, where the food is cooked right and rhe staff gives a care.</Text>

<Rating>1< /Rating>< Review>
The most disappointing, humiliating,and shocking experience i have ever had here. Kaylin the waitress and Miguel the manager were rude and disrespectful beyond belief. Basically it felt like i was in an embarrassing dream. My family has been coming here for years, long before it got so busy. This particular night it was my daughter and i. It started out by waiting for over an hour to be seated when we were told it would be 30 min. Ok so thats understandable since they were busy. The craziness began when we asked for fries while we were deciding what to order. (Which we'd always done in the past without any problem) We were told by the waitress (kaylin) that we could only get fries if we were ordering them with our meals. We'd never been told that before but my daughter said she was going to order the clucks and fries so we were covered. She took our order and i asked for more fries and some ranch to go with them. She left and came back empty handed and preceded to tell me that only my daughter could have fries cuz they come with her meal and i ordered fruit not fries. I said "fine i wont eat any of them", but i was becoming increasingly offended by her condescending attitude and quite frankly confused by the entire conversation.  As if we were trying to steal fries. I had never felt so harrassed for asking for fries. She said it wasn't her that makes the rules it was her manager (Miguel) and she didnt care if i ate the fries. So why the hell are we having this conversation then???. I asked for the check cuz by now we are both completely digusted with this place. She leaves and the manager walks over and just stands at our table staring at my daughter not saying a word. I'm waiting for his excellant customer service to kick in but it never came. I broke the awkward silence by asking for the check so i could pay for our drinks and fries. He told us not to worry about it. So i didnt!!!  Oh i would like to add from a previous visit. The waiters do tip themselves. So check your charges. They add their own tips on to the bill whether they deserve it or not.< /Review>
